  <input type="text" placeholder="Search..." />
  <i class="bi bi-search search-icon"></i>
  <button class="clear-btn" type="button" aria-label="Clear search">
    <i class="bi bi-x-lg"></i>
  </button>
</div>
```

Rules to add:

1. `.search-wrapper` — the wrapper replaces the bare input as a direct flex child of `.toolbar`. Set:
   - `position: relative;`
   - `display: inline-flex;`
   - `align-items: center;`
   - `margin-left: auto;` (pushes the search to the right, replacing the margin-left:auto that was on the bare input)

2. `.search-wrapper input[type='text']` — override the inherited `.toolbar input[type='text']` margin:
   - `margin-left: 0;` (the wrapper handles positioning now)
   - `padding-right: 28px;` (prevents typed text from going under the absolutely-positioned icon)

3. `.search-wrapper .search-icon` and `.search-wrapper .clear-btn` — position both icons inside the input, right-aligned:
   - `position: absolute;`
   - `right: 6px;`
   - `color: #9a9a9a;` (muted foreground, matching the theme)
   - `pointer-events: none;` for `.search-icon` (it's decorative; the clear button needs to be clickable so do NOT set pointer-events:none on `.clear-btn`)
   - For `.clear-btn` additionally: `background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; padding: 2px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; line-height: 1;`
   - Add `.clear-btn:hover { color: #e6e6e6; }`

4. Visibility toggling via `:placeholder-shown` (no JavaScript needed). The icon and button are SIBLINGS after the input, so the general sibling combinator `~` works:
   - Default state (input empty / placeholder shown): show search icon, hide clear button:
     ```css
     .search-wrapper .clear-btn { display: none; }
     ```
   - When input has text (placeholder NOT shown): hide search icon, show clear button:
     ```css
     .search-wrapper input:not(:placeholder-shown) ~ .search-icon { display: none; }
     .search-wrapper input:not(:placeholder-shown) ~ .clear-btn { display: inline-flex; }
     ```

5. Spinner animation — place these at the end of the file:
   ```css
   @keyframes spin {
     to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
   }
   .spinning {
     animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
     display: inline-block;
   }
   .search-spinner {
     display: flex;
     justify-content: center;
     align-items: center;
     padding: 16px;
     color: #9a9a9a;
     font-size: 20px;
   }
   ```

Do NOT modify any existing CSS rules. Only ADD new rules.

Verification: Run `npx vitest run src/app.css.test.ts` — existing tests should still pass. New CSS-specific tests will be added in a later task.

